This switch is packaged as a 'desktop' formfactor unit.
:This is to say that the power and network cables plug in on the opposite side of the indicator LEDs. Hardware revision '''V1.0R''' of the '''TEG-S80g''' provides link-speed LEDs and a two mounting holes on the bottom. :Later revisions of '''TEG-S80g''' remove both these features. :This may be noteworthy to some, as evidenced by a handful of [https://www.amazon.com/gp/customer-reviews/R1EMANSHO9SQA1 Amazon][https://www.amazon.com/gp/customer-reviews/R32QW31YZJT1WB ] and [https://www.newegg.com/Product/SingleProductReview.aspx?ReviewID=4130806 Newegg][https://www.newegg.com/Product/SingleProductReview.aspx?ReviewID=4097944 ] reviewers.
